# Design Style Guardrail

Use the visual language introduced in commit `ce2331d` and the primitives in `app/globals.css`.

## Source Of Truth

- Prefer existing design tokens from `:root` in `app/globals.css` (`--background`, `--foreground`, `--palette-*`, `--cta-*`).
- Reuse existing utility/component classes before creating new one-off styles (`btn-neo-brutalist`, `btn-neo-brutalist-cta`, `romanian-neo-brut`, etc.).
- Keep color usage token-based (`hsl(var(--token))`) instead of raw hex values in components.

## Style Direction

- Apple-inspired baseline: clean spacing, restrained typography, clear hierarchy, minimal visual noise.
- Essentialist composition: fewer elements, stronger intent, no decorative complexity without purpose.
- Neo-brutalist accents: sharp edges, visible borders, bold offset shadows, high-contrast highlights.
- Balance matters: keep most layouts calm/minimal; apply neo-brutal accents to CTA, tags, badges, and emphasis surfaces.

## Implementation Rules

- Prefer Tailwind utility classes + shared classes in `globals.css`; avoid inline style objects unless strictly needed.
- Keep interactions simple and tactile (small translate + shadow shifts on hover/active).
- Use `font-heading` for headings and preserve current `Inter` + `Sora` pairing.
- Do not introduce a second visual system that conflicts with existing tokens, radii, or shadow language.
